12.4 billion\nyears into cosmic history. Attempts to interpret the results from these 10\nH$_2$ absorbers in terms of a spatial variation of $\\mu$ are currently hampered\nby the small sample size and their coincidental distribution in a relatively\nnarrow band across the sky.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 13 Nov 2015 22:52:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-05-25"}
